HEADWORD: Prefecundation
<hw>Pre*fec`un*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A term collectively applied to the changes or
conditions preceding fecundation, especially to the changes which the
ovum undergoes before fecundation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefecundatory</ent>⟦br⟧
